result.execSummary:
The defendant Edwynn Orlando White was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting/Obstructing an Officer. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Edwynn Orlando White in court with attorney Elizabeth A Carlson.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to RESISTING/OBSTRUCTING AN OFFICER contrary to County Ordinance 63.05(2) to which the defendant entered a plea of guilty.  Court found the defendant guilty and ordered the defendant to pay a forfeiture in the amount of $75.00 including costs to be aid by 02-22-2016 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Defendant Edwynn Orlando White in court with attorney Elizabeth A Carlson.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm. Jury trial scheduled for December 16, 2015 at 08:30 am.
